Possible changes for 0.9 (Cygwin 1.7):

* Fix rcs tarball names to allow more than one at a time
* Delete prep_scrollkeeper_omf, no longer needed with rarian
* autotools: move cygautoreconf and cygconf here, and auto-inherit (?)
* berkdb: remove java
* cmake: move cygcmake here (?)
* cross: overhaul, support mingw (perhaps separate mingw.cygclass)
* emacs: not working, remove (?)
* fox: change to wxwidgets-like fox-config wrapper
* gst-plugins0.8: remove (?)
* mono: remove -j1, move to .cygport's
* qt3: separate qt3-qmake from qt3
* svn: fix SVN_MODULE
* xorg: rename font-* packages; build shared/static


GOALS for 0.3 development:

* Custom commands (CW)
* warnings for deprecated APIs
* Debug and/or Verbose mode
* Additional cygclasses:
	- alternatives
	- relocate: http://cygwin.com/ml/cygwin/2006-10/msg00743.html
* Check postinstalls for absolute paths
* Fix all FIXMEs


The rest is a wishlist of features to add in future releases, in no
particular order:

* Documentation (man/info/HTML ??)
* Complete test suite
* NLS
* Additional cygclasses:
	- doxygen
* Additional mirrors:
	- kernel
	- mysql
* dolocale
* dosed
* multiple-patch tarballs in cygpatch
* Windows shortcuts for X11 programs
	doico /path/to/pixmap.png [calls png(to|2)ico and doins]
	make_win_shortcut Foo [run.exe foo.exe -wait --display=...]
* error(): use 'caller' builtin?
